WEBVTT

00:02.170 --> 00:04.272
This will catch on.
Those two always together.

00:04.305 --> 00:06.941
Not when they rolled up on me.
Just Lenny.

00:06.975 --> 00:09.744
Nah, that can't be right.
(gunshot)

00:09.778 --> 00:11.813
LEON: Don't tell me.
I was there.

00:11.846 --> 00:15.483
It's all destroyed --
the camp, our pipeline.

00:15.516 --> 00:17.285
I have other suppliers
we can use for now.

00:17.318 --> 00:19.654
(camera shutter clicks)
TEDDY: The Colombians?

00:19.688 --> 00:21.255
That's Jess, right?

00:21.289 --> 00:23.658
And him, you know,
Latin Freddie Mercury.

00:23.692 --> 00:26.360
You have the balls to come in
here after running to daddy?

00:26.394 --> 00:27.796
You want me to run.

00:27.829 --> 00:29.630
(speaks Spanish)

00:29.664 --> 00:34.635
We have to talk about what's
gonna happen with the business.

00:40.474 --> 00:43.177
(engine rumbling)

00:43.211 --> 00:45.880
(brakes squeal)

00:45.914 --> 00:48.182
(engine stops,
dog barking in distance)

00:48.216 --> 00:51.219
Thanks for the lift, man,
for letting me crash.

00:51.252 --> 00:54.188
Anytime, my brother.
You give Leon my best.

00:54.222 --> 00:55.623
(zips bag)

00:55.656 --> 00:57.291
If you need to talk,

00:57.325 --> 00:58.993
you know
I'm here for you, okay?

00:59.027 --> 01:01.395
(laughs) All right, man. Thanks.

01:01.429 --> 01:04.833
All right. Also...

01:04.866 --> 01:07.135
you got any more
of that crack stuff,

01:07.168 --> 01:08.669
I'd definitely be interested.

01:08.703 --> 01:10.872
I got you.

01:10.905 --> 01:12.506
Rad!
(engine starts)

01:12.540 --> 01:13.975
Oh, don't forget.

01:14.008 --> 01:16.544
Up there to the left. Freeway.
All right?

01:16.577 --> 01:20.181
-I remember.
-Don't get lost again!

01:20.214 --> 01:21.515
♪♪

01:21.549 --> 01:24.518
(door creaks closed)

01:28.222 --> 01:30.258
Still going good, huh?

01:30.291 --> 01:32.060
It's better than good,
nephew.

01:32.093 --> 01:34.362
I don't know why you sleepin'
over that white boy house

01:34.395 --> 01:36.597
like we ain't got
a perfectly good couch.

01:36.630 --> 01:40.534
Think you just answered
your own question.

01:40.568 --> 01:42.270
You was out late
last night.

01:42.303 --> 01:44.572
You damn right I was.

01:44.605 --> 01:48.376
And look, we got to re-up
on this powder.

01:48.409 --> 01:50.178
No problem.

01:50.211 --> 01:53.948
You got any idea where we gon'
cook up the next batch?

01:53.982 --> 01:57.051
♪♪

01:57.085 --> 02:00.789
I know you ain't just look at
my kitchen like you plan to use.

02:00.822 --> 02:02.757
We gonna rent a place.

02:02.791 --> 02:05.459
Somewhere we can store it
and cook the product.

02:05.493 --> 02:08.096
All right, Louie,
I'm-a put you on that.

02:08.129 --> 02:09.931
Go see Walter.
He'll hook it up.

02:09.964 --> 02:12.033
♪♪

02:12.066 --> 02:13.902
Boy, we gotta talk turkey.

02:13.935 --> 02:16.570
I feel like the product's
priced right.

02:16.604 --> 02:18.606
I ain't talkin' 'bout
the product.

02:18.639 --> 02:21.475
Now when
you first came to me,

02:21.509 --> 02:24.245
you said we was gonna split
this down the middle, 50/50.

02:24.278 --> 02:27.315
Then what you do? Huh?

02:27.348 --> 02:30.151
You turn me away.

02:30.184 --> 02:31.752
I've done all
the heavy lifting, huh?

02:31.786 --> 02:33.654
I'm not giving half away now.

02:33.687 --> 02:36.991
(laughs) You ain't givin' shit,
all right?

02:37.025 --> 02:38.592
Now I'm earnin' it.

02:38.626 --> 02:40.461
You need a partner, not them
little knuckleheads

02:40.494 --> 02:42.130
you be runnin' around with.

02:42.163 --> 02:45.399
You need somebody that know
the game, got some cred.

02:45.433 --> 02:47.902
Set your little narrow ass
straight.

02:47.936 --> 02:51.806
It's my connect, my product,
my process.

02:51.840 --> 02:55.509
I've already got Lee and Kev
to take care of.

02:55.543 --> 02:59.914
(bills rustling)

02:59.948 --> 03:02.750
(sighs)
I can give y'all 10%.

03:02.783 --> 03:05.219
-Shit, you trippin'.
-Woman.

03:06.454 --> 03:07.688
40%.

03:07.721 --> 03:09.924
20 and even that's
pushin' it.

03:09.958 --> 03:11.592
(bills rustling)

03:11.625 --> 03:14.095
(laughs)

03:14.128 --> 03:16.197
-25%, we straight.
-Deal.

03:16.230 --> 03:19.934
Yeah! That's my family
right there! Hey?

03:19.968 --> 03:22.871
Move that. I'm-a take a shit.
Y'all gon' keep counting that.

03:22.904 --> 03:24.438
(beads rustle)

03:24.472 --> 03:26.640
(door opens, closes)

03:26.674 --> 03:29.010
(dog barking in distance)
Mm.

03:30.411 --> 03:33.848
Ray-Ray thinkin' on it.

03:33.882 --> 03:35.449
Should know soon.

03:35.483 --> 03:38.052
Either way, you're gon'
take care of me, right?

03:38.086 --> 03:41.155
I got you.

03:41.189 --> 03:44.058
What about you?
You all right?

03:44.092 --> 03:47.161
You juggling
a lot of shit.

03:47.195 --> 03:49.463
You doin' okay?

03:49.497 --> 03:51.065
Mm.

03:53.501 --> 03:57.805
(sighs)

03:57.838 --> 04:00.841
♪♪

04:12.520 --> 04:16.524
I will make this go away.
Just like I said that I would.

04:16.557 --> 04:19.060
But I do need one thing from you
to make it happen.

04:19.093 --> 04:22.763
What? Need you to leave
town for a little while.

04:22.796 --> 04:24.065
How long?

04:24.098 --> 04:26.834
Just a month.
Maybe two at the most.

04:26.867 --> 04:28.937
No. That's not possible.

04:28.970 --> 04:31.272
Look, you saw what she did
with the flyers of Kristin.

04:31.305 --> 04:33.942
Right? This is gonna be
so much worse.

04:33.975 --> 04:35.743
She's gonna go to the cops
if she hasn't already.

04:35.776 --> 04:37.578
And then she's gonna go
to the newspapers

04:37.611 --> 04:40.748
and the evening news and your
face is gonna be everywhere.

04:40.781 --> 04:43.084
In two days, I'm making a deal
with the Colombians.

04:43.117 --> 04:45.686
And if I disappear,
so will they.

04:45.719 --> 04:47.455
You'll have no one
to fly the shipment.

04:47.488 --> 04:49.257
No, I can find another pilot.

04:49.290 --> 04:50.624
And you'll still deal
with the Colombians.

04:50.658 --> 04:52.460
You just won't be
doing it from here.

04:52.493 --> 04:56.564
Or I take care of the girl
and nothing changes.

04:56.597 --> 04:59.100
(utensil clatters)

04:59.133 --> 05:00.868
Look... (sighs)

05:00.901 --> 05:03.537
If she goes missing,
especially now,

05:03.571 --> 05:06.040
after finding this,
that's gonna look terrible.

05:06.074 --> 05:08.209
They'll think she ran away
just like her sister.

05:08.242 --> 05:10.444
No, it is too big of a risk. We're
not there yet. (utensil clatters)

05:10.478 --> 05:12.981
And what if you're wrong, hmm?
And you can't stop her?

05:13.014 --> 05:14.782
I can control this.

05:14.815 --> 05:18.119
I can. I-I -- I'll ramp up
surveillance on her apartment.

05:18.152 --> 05:19.820
I'll put a full tap
on her phone.

05:19.853 --> 05:22.490
I will use all of the company
resources to discredit her

05:22.523 --> 05:23.992
and steer her off the path.

05:24.025 --> 05:29.263
I just need you to please
help me do my job.

05:31.265 --> 05:33.767
Okay.

05:43.444 --> 05:47.315
(footsteps depart)

05:47.348 --> 05:50.318
♪♪

05:50.351 --> 05:53.387
(men singing in Spanish)

05:57.658 --> 05:59.793
Might have something for you,
Ray.

05:59.827 --> 06:03.664
I have something to share
with you folks, okay?

06:03.697 --> 06:07.168
Come inside. I'm gonna have one
of my guys call you.

06:07.201 --> 06:10.204
Nothing heavy. Take a look.

06:10.238 --> 06:12.673
Here.

06:12.706 --> 06:16.510
(exhales deeply)

06:16.544 --> 06:20.581
♪♪

06:22.683 --> 06:25.386
Remember your cousin Antonio
from San Diego?

06:25.419 --> 06:29.723
Yeah, I remember his breath
stank something awful.

06:29.757 --> 06:34.895
Graduated from San Diego State.
Business and accounting.

06:34.928 --> 06:37.665
You're doing this now?

06:37.698 --> 06:41.235
You said you were fine.

06:41.269 --> 06:43.304
And just because your father
has passed away

06:43.337 --> 06:44.972
does not mean
business stops.

06:45.005 --> 06:47.108
It's not stopping.

06:48.876 --> 06:51.712
I'm handling the books.

06:51.745 --> 06:54.548
When I'm ready to take on
someone new, I'll let you know.

06:54.582 --> 06:58.086
You're gonna let me know?

07:00.421 --> 07:03.157
(footsteps approach)

07:03.191 --> 07:05.326
(Indistinct conversations
in Spanish)

07:05.359 --> 07:06.894
MAN: Señora.

07:08.596 --> 07:10.398
Señora.

07:21.142 --> 07:23.144
(sighs)

07:38.226 --> 07:40.794
(exhales)

07:40.828 --> 07:42.463
(kiss)

07:50.504 --> 07:52.773
(pats shoulder)

07:57.111 --> 07:58.346
(speaks Spanish)

08:04.084 --> 08:06.454
(speaks Spanish)

08:06.487 --> 08:08.856
Mm.

08:26.374 --> 08:27.608
(cries)

08:27.641 --> 08:29.277
(sniffles)

08:29.310 --> 08:32.313
(continues crying)

08:35.649 --> 08:38.619
(doors creaking open)

08:42.890 --> 08:46.660
(doors close)

08:49.630 --> 08:50.931
(keys jingle)

08:50.964 --> 08:54.134
Mom?
Whatchu doin' home?

08:54.168 --> 08:56.370
I could ask you
the same question.

08:56.404 --> 08:58.839
Where you been sleepin'?
Jerome's?

08:58.872 --> 09:01.041
Volpe's.

09:01.074 --> 09:03.377
I just came home to shower,
grab some clothes.

09:03.411 --> 09:06.046
You all right?

09:06.079 --> 09:07.648
(scoffs)

09:07.681 --> 09:10.218
Listen, Mom, I'm sorry
I lied to you.

09:10.251 --> 09:11.852
It was disrespectful,

09:11.885 --> 09:15.456
and I should've treated you
better than that.

09:15.489 --> 09:17.658
Talk to me.

09:19.993 --> 09:22.730
Tulf fired me.

09:22.763 --> 09:25.399
What?

09:25.433 --> 09:27.668
W-why?

09:27.701 --> 09:30.238
I called his ass out.

09:30.271 --> 09:31.872
Told him to put me on them
Westside properties

09:31.905 --> 09:34.742
like he'd been promisin'.

09:34.775 --> 09:36.810
Said things had changed,

09:36.844 --> 09:39.213
that he needed to sell it.

09:39.247 --> 09:42.383
(chuckles) That I'd have
other opportunities.

09:42.416 --> 09:44.151
I don't know exactly
what happened then.

09:44.184 --> 09:47.221
I just know I saw red,
and I went after him and...

09:47.255 --> 09:50.658
(sighs) When it was done,
I was bein' tossed out.

09:50.691 --> 09:52.192
Fuck Tulfowitz.

09:52.226 --> 09:54.928
-(scoffs)
-You hear me?

09:54.962 --> 09:57.598
And all the shit
he put you through.

09:57.631 --> 10:00.167
Fuck him.

10:00.200 --> 10:01.869
This is a good thing.

10:04.037 --> 10:06.374
-This is a good thing?
-Mm-hmm.

10:06.407 --> 10:08.709
That was my job, Franklin.

10:08.742 --> 10:11.679
You'll get another job.
One that deserves you.

10:11.712 --> 10:13.714
Where? Doin' what?

10:13.747 --> 10:15.883
I killed myself trying
to make that man happy,

10:15.916 --> 10:17.785
and now I just
threw it all away.

10:17.818 --> 10:20.087
Tulf ain't gonna give me
no references.

10:20.120 --> 10:22.089
There's bills
and then the mortgage.

10:22.122 --> 10:25.693
You ain't gonna worry about
any of that anymore, Mom.

10:25.726 --> 10:28.095
Huh?

10:30.631 --> 10:32.566
Unh-unh.
(money thuds)

10:32.600 --> 10:34.602
I don't want
your reefer money.

10:36.470 --> 10:38.138
(footsteps depart)

10:38.171 --> 10:40.441
(sighs)

10:43.110 --> 10:44.645
(closes drawer)

10:47.915 --> 10:50.484
(siren wailing in distance)

10:59.026 --> 11:01.429
(zips bag)

11:20.213 --> 11:22.015
(door creaks open)

11:22.049 --> 11:25.185
No, you can, uh, leave the robe
at home this time, just, uh,

11:25.218 --> 11:27.855
keep an eye on things
while I'm in there.

11:27.888 --> 11:30.691
Yeah, okay. Thanks.
I'll see you soon.

11:30.724 --> 11:32.360
(receiver clatters)

11:37.698 --> 11:41.335
(horn honks in distance)

11:43.637 --> 11:46.006
(dialing)

11:46.039 --> 11:49.142
(line rings) VICTORIA: Hi. If you
have any information on Kristin,

11:49.176 --> 11:53.514
please leave your name and --
(receiver clatters)

11:53.547 --> 11:55.182
(lock clicks)

12:00.754 --> 12:03.357
(opens and closes drawer)

12:04.758 --> 12:07.395
(clicking)

12:12.866 --> 12:14.334
♪♪

12:14.368 --> 12:16.069
Doesn't change a thing.

12:16.103 --> 12:18.939
(speaking Spanish)

12:21.108 --> 12:23.243
Fuck, yeah.
That's the best time.

12:23.276 --> 12:28.382
Whole family in one place.
Drunk, tired, easy pickings.

12:28.416 --> 12:30.584
You know where they're having
the velario?

12:33.754 --> 12:36.056
I want you to go, Gustavo,
check the place out,

12:36.089 --> 12:37.658
see how many people
we're gonna need,

12:37.691 --> 12:39.226
what the layout looks like.

12:40.561 --> 12:43.564
(door creaking)

12:45.232 --> 12:47.134
(door closes)
Oso.

12:50.070 --> 12:51.872
Almost there, vato.

12:51.905 --> 12:55.108
Don't bitch out now.

12:55.142 --> 12:58.378
(Dog barking,
rooster crowing in distance)

12:58.412 --> 13:01.415
(muffled TV playing)

13:08.388 --> 13:10.424
(lock clicks)

13:10.458 --> 13:12.926
(door creaking)

13:12.960 --> 13:15.729
Victoria?

13:15.763 --> 13:20.434
(static)

13:20.468 --> 13:23.437
(voices speaking indistinctly
on TV)

13:23.471 --> 13:26.474
(tool whirring in distance)

13:32.312 --> 13:35.916
(whirring continues)

13:48.195 --> 13:51.264
(whirring continues)

13:51.298 --> 13:54.935
Alejandro.

13:54.968 --> 13:56.904
(whirring stops)

13:56.937 --> 13:59.507
Get out of here, Teddy.

14:01.174 --> 14:03.210
No, I can't do that.

14:09.449 --> 14:12.686
Of course you can. It's the
easiest thing in the world.

14:12.720 --> 14:17.257
Just turn around, walk out,

14:17.290 --> 14:18.759
close the door behind you.

14:18.792 --> 14:21.261
(exhales sharply)

14:21.294 --> 14:23.030
(strained voice)
This isn't right.

14:23.063 --> 14:25.165
Isn't right?

14:26.534 --> 14:28.869
(chuckles)

14:28.902 --> 14:32.205
This is a war, Teddy.

14:32.239 --> 14:33.807
We do what is required of us,

14:33.841 --> 14:37.177
which is exactly what I did
that night at the house,

14:37.210 --> 14:41.615
and unfortunately, what you are
incapable of doing.

14:41.649 --> 14:45.052
So I'm doing this
for both of us.

14:45.085 --> 14:46.720
This is my gift to you.

14:46.754 --> 14:49.122
All you have to do is...

14:49.156 --> 14:52.425
accept it.

14:55.362 --> 14:59.166
(breathes unevenly)

15:03.003 --> 15:06.640
You're doing great, Teddy.

15:06.674 --> 15:09.643
-(exhales sharply)
-You're a hero.

15:09.677 --> 15:12.980
See you soon, okay?

15:13.013 --> 15:16.016
(breathes unevenly)

15:21.589 --> 15:24.558
(whirring resumes)

15:43.777 --> 15:47.414
(whirring continues)

15:47.447 --> 15:49.116
(whirring stops,
TV playing indistinctly)

15:49.149 --> 15:51.118
(gunshot, thud)

15:51.151 --> 15:54.521
(breathing heavily)

15:54.554 --> 15:57.224
(TV continues playing
indistinctly)

16:01.294 --> 16:03.363
(exhales deeply)

16:03.396 --> 16:07.334
(TV continues playing
indistinctly)

16:15.408 --> 16:18.211
(speaking Hebrew)
Fucking shit.

16:18.245 --> 16:21.248
(continues speaking in Hebrew)

16:24.952 --> 16:26.720
What's up with
these crates here?

16:26.754 --> 16:28.622
What crates?

16:28.656 --> 16:30.323
These crates.

16:30.357 --> 16:32.225
♪♪

16:32.259 --> 16:34.594
Motherfucker!

16:34.628 --> 16:36.496
-Yuda...
-YUDA: Huh?

16:36.529 --> 16:41.601
(speaking Hebrew)

16:41.635 --> 16:44.905
Did you know Franklin
saved Yuda's life?

16:44.938 --> 16:46.907
-You know that?
-No.

16:46.940 --> 16:49.442
It's true. Yeah.
He's a good boy. (laughs)

16:49.476 --> 16:51.011
So every time he come here,

16:51.044 --> 16:54.514
I offer him a drink,
some snort, some pink.

16:54.547 --> 16:57.150
He always say no.

16:57.184 --> 16:59.119
Shit, I'm good with
any one of those.

16:59.152 --> 17:02.322
Well, I didn't offer it
to you, did I?

17:02.355 --> 17:04.191
♪♪

17:04.224 --> 17:05.859
(bottle clatters)

17:05.893 --> 17:08.195
Fuck did you bring them
here for?

17:08.228 --> 17:10.297
Told you.
Business is ramping up.

17:10.330 --> 17:13.100
Means we're gonna buy more.
Pay upfront.

17:13.133 --> 17:15.869
That also means might not always
be me here making the runs.

17:15.903 --> 17:20.040
Oh, yes, it will.
It's you I like, you I trust.

17:20.073 --> 17:22.109
You put on the vest.

17:22.142 --> 17:23.510
♪♪

17:28.381 --> 17:29.983
(laughs)

17:30.017 --> 17:31.819
Hey, you know, Avi,

17:31.852 --> 17:33.787
seeing as that we gonna be,

17:33.821 --> 17:36.857
you know, buying in bulk,
paying upfront,

17:36.890 --> 17:39.960
how 'bout we do a little bit
better on that price?

17:39.993 --> 17:41.461
What?

17:41.494 --> 17:43.997
I know you started the boy
off at 12.

17:44.031 --> 17:45.899
You fronting the shit,
he don't know no better.

17:45.933 --> 17:48.568
Now this shit is real.

17:48.601 --> 17:50.838
How 'bout you shave
a little off that price?

17:50.871 --> 17:54.541
Oh. Maybe.

17:54.574 --> 17:58.211
-(Chuckling) Yeah.
-Yeah, maybe.

17:58.245 --> 18:01.014
Or maybe I'll shave the eyebrows
off your face

18:01.048 --> 18:03.583
and tell you to go suck
on a donkey's dick.

18:03.616 --> 18:06.153
Uh, Avi, 12 is fine, all right?

18:06.186 --> 18:09.022
Fuck is this? I let you bring
your friends into my house,

18:09.056 --> 18:11.258
and you fucking strong arm me?

18:11.291 --> 18:13.326
Hey, look, nobody trying
to strong arm nobody.

18:13.360 --> 18:17.998
♪♪

18:18.031 --> 18:19.432
Hell you're not.

18:19.466 --> 18:22.535
♪♪

18:22.569 --> 18:25.105
And just so you know who's
in fucking charge here,

18:25.138 --> 18:26.606
it's gonna be 13 a key.

18:26.639 --> 18:29.376
-Come on, Avi.
-Keep on talkin'. It'll be 14.

18:29.409 --> 18:31.544
Or you can go someplace else.

18:31.578 --> 18:35.115
You greedy motherfuckas.

18:35.148 --> 18:38.151
♪♪

18:54.167 --> 18:56.703
Now get the fuck out.
(bag zips)

18:56.736 --> 18:59.773
♪♪

19:04.344 --> 19:06.246
(kisses)

19:06.279 --> 19:09.783
♪♪

19:12.752 --> 19:14.587
I asked y'all to be cool.

19:14.621 --> 19:17.124
Hey, man, it ain't our fault
the dude is crazy, cuz.

19:17.157 --> 19:18.892
Hey, man, he more than crazy.
Motherfucker's racist.

19:18.926 --> 19:21.294
It doesn't matter.

19:21.328 --> 19:23.263
Unless y'all know where I can
get pure product

19:23.296 --> 19:25.298
at those prices,
Avi's our guy.

19:25.332 --> 19:26.766
I know where you get the product
at a better price

19:26.800 --> 19:28.568
and you ain't gotta deal
with no crazy ass Jew.

19:28.601 --> 19:30.437
Look, he getting it
from somewhere,

19:30.470 --> 19:31.972
and it's much less
than 12 a key.

19:32.005 --> 19:33.974
Now you have somebody
stake out his little crib,

19:34.007 --> 19:36.609
see who comes and goes,

19:36.643 --> 19:38.145
get right to the source.

19:41.148 --> 19:44.084
Can't just sit outside
his house and wait.

19:44.117 --> 19:46.786
Be arrested in five minutes
in this neighborhood.

19:46.820 --> 19:51.391
You right. We can't.
But you know someone who can.

19:54.694 --> 19:57.597
(lock turns)

19:57.630 --> 19:59.532
(bird cawing)

19:59.566 --> 20:00.968
(keys jingle and thud)

20:01.001 --> 20:03.904
(door creaks closed)

20:13.346 --> 20:15.182
(object clatters)

20:25.725 --> 20:28.828
(Train whistle blowing
in distance)

20:34.067 --> 20:36.970
(machine beeps, click)
JULIA: Hey, it's me.

20:37.004 --> 20:39.072
Uh, haven't heard from you
in a couple of days.

20:39.106 --> 20:41.741
Starting to get
a little worried.

20:41.774 --> 20:43.810
Could you please just give me
a call when you get a chance?

20:43.843 --> 20:45.478
(baby whining)

20:45.512 --> 20:47.647
Are you okay, honey?
You a little bit hungry?

20:47.680 --> 20:51.551
Oh, you wanna say hi? Wanna say hi?
(shower running)

20:51.584 --> 20:57.024
Dada... Uh, all right.
I hope you're okay.

20:57.057 --> 20:59.927
Um...love you. Bye.

20:59.960 --> 21:01.361
(machine beeps and clicks)

21:01.394 --> 21:04.397
(shower continues running)

21:13.606 --> 21:16.209
♪♪

21:16.243 --> 21:20.013
(Indistinct conversations
in Spanish)

21:20.047 --> 21:23.783
(speaking Spanish)

21:32.292 --> 21:35.095
(pouring liquor)

21:35.128 --> 21:37.297
No...

21:42.635 --> 21:44.171
Hmm.

21:54.814 --> 21:56.449
No, mi amor...

22:04.924 --> 22:06.459
(scoffs)

22:38.891 --> 22:40.893
Hija...

22:53.073 --> 22:57.710
(door opens, closes)

23:01.648 --> 23:04.651
(muffled voices speaking
indistinctly)

23:15.362 --> 23:17.897
(vehicles passing)

23:17.930 --> 23:21.401
(indistinct conversation
in distance)

23:37.950 --> 23:41.154
(inhales deeply)

23:41.188 --> 23:44.224
Smoke with me?

23:44.257 --> 23:47.427
(speaks Spanish)

23:49.896 --> 23:52.899
Maybe you're smoking
the wrong shit.

23:52.932 --> 23:54.667
Yeah, maybe.

23:54.701 --> 24:00.073
(inhales sharply)

24:00.107 --> 24:02.275
(exhales deeply)

24:02.309 --> 24:04.043
(siren wailing in distance)

24:04.077 --> 24:07.280
Ramiro's bringing someone in
to learn the books.

24:07.314 --> 24:11.184
(laughs)

24:11.218 --> 24:13.853
You laugh 'cause you know
you were right.

24:13.886 --> 24:15.655
Mm.

24:23.330 --> 24:26.199
Why are you still here?

24:26.233 --> 24:30.270
Because I have faith
in you, chola.

24:30.303 --> 24:31.971
Yeah, seriously.

24:32.004 --> 24:35.007
We can run this business
together.

24:41.781 --> 24:44.617
What if I told you
I don't believe you?

24:47.587 --> 24:51.291
...or paranoid.

24:51.324 --> 24:55.162
(inhales sharply)

24:55.195 --> 24:57.497
(exhales deeply)

25:01.601 --> 25:05.672
That if I go through with this,
I'm not doing it for you.

25:05.705 --> 25:07.640
I know.

25:07.674 --> 25:12.011
(sighs)

25:12.044 --> 25:14.781
And I have to be there.

25:14.814 --> 25:17.650
So they won't think I had
anything to do with it.

25:30.897 --> 25:33.300
Okay.

25:33.333 --> 25:36.969
Call Stomper.
Tell him I wanna meet.

25:39.806 --> 25:41.874
(lighter clatters)

25:43.310 --> 25:44.977
(lighter clicks)

25:45.011 --> 25:47.046
(lighter clatters)

25:50.917 --> 25:53.152
(exhales deeply)

25:58.525 --> 25:59.726
(dog barking in distance)

25:59.759 --> 26:02.061
Sure you good
to be out here?

26:02.094 --> 26:05.198
Yeah. Need to get out that
madhouse for a minute.

26:05.232 --> 26:08.100
That laid up shit
getting old already.

26:10.270 --> 26:12.071
What?

26:12.104 --> 26:13.640
Nothin'.

26:13.673 --> 26:16.409
Bullshit. You got somethin',
don't you?

26:16.443 --> 26:19.679
(indistinct conversations)

26:19.712 --> 26:21.814
Made a couple moves
with Ray-Ray.

26:21.848 --> 26:23.850
Think I got
everything set up.

26:23.883 --> 26:25.918
-All right, then, I'll be there.
-No, man.

26:25.952 --> 26:27.654
You're gonna be a liability,
and you know it.

26:27.687 --> 26:30.823
I mean, fuck that shit, cuz.

26:30.857 --> 26:33.893
Look, man, for real.

26:33.926 --> 26:37.564
Sit this one out.
I got it.

26:37.597 --> 26:39.866
(siren wailing in distance)

26:39.899 --> 26:42.735
(Man shouts indistinctly
in distance)

26:42.769 --> 26:46.406
Hey, Frank.

26:46.439 --> 26:48.174
When you had that gun
on Carvel,

26:48.207 --> 26:50.410
what were you thinkin' about?
What stopped you?

26:50.443 --> 26:55.515
I don't know.
A lot of shit, I guess.

26:55.548 --> 26:58.451
Well, when you dealing
with Ray-Ray and Lenny,

26:58.485 --> 27:00.186
I want you to think about
taking care of your people,

27:00.219 --> 27:01.921
your folk.

27:01.954 --> 27:06.092
Your moms, your uncle,
Louie, Melody.

27:06.125 --> 27:07.794
I even want you
to think about me

27:07.827 --> 27:09.028
bleeding on that fucking ground
and you pull that trigger.

27:09.061 --> 27:10.263
You hear me?

27:13.500 --> 27:17.069
You eat them or they eat you,
that's all.

27:21.073 --> 27:23.643
We gonna be good, man.

27:23.676 --> 27:26.679
(indistinct conversations)

27:33.119 --> 27:36.122
(fast-paced classical
piano piece playing)

27:50.603 --> 27:53.172
(knock on door)

27:53.205 --> 27:54.574
♪♪

27:54.607 --> 27:55.842
Teddy.

27:59.111 --> 28:01.514
(pounding on door)

28:01.548 --> 28:03.616
♪♪

28:03.650 --> 28:05.718
(button clicks, music stops)

28:12.291 --> 28:16.463
(door creaks)

28:16.496 --> 28:18.865
H-hey. (clears throat)

28:20.132 --> 28:22.835
You don't answer
your phone?

28:24.537 --> 28:27.340
(door creaks closed)

28:27.374 --> 28:29.208
(horns honking in distance)

28:29.241 --> 28:31.678
-(sighs)
-Julia called.

28:31.711 --> 28:33.813
Said she hadn't heard from you
in a couple of days

28:33.846 --> 28:37.817
and was worried there might be
something wrong.

28:37.850 --> 28:43.356
(sighs) Things, um, um...

28:48.428 --> 28:52.264
Get dressed, Teddy.

28:54.934 --> 28:56.335
Okay.

28:56.369 --> 28:58.371
I didn't know you were
a classical fan.

28:58.405 --> 29:01.808
Who was that? Chopin?

29:01.841 --> 29:03.743
♪♪

29:03.776 --> 29:07.580
James, I don't think
I'm the guy for this.

29:07.614 --> 29:10.483
♪♪

29:10.517 --> 29:13.986
I went to bat for you,
Teddy.

29:14.020 --> 29:16.055
I'm sorry.

29:16.088 --> 29:18.157
Want my advice?

29:18.190 --> 29:19.992
You need to learn
to let things go.

29:20.026 --> 29:23.162
I mean, come on, this is just
like Tehran all over again.

29:23.195 --> 29:26.499
Sometimes shit just goes wrong
in our business.

29:26.533 --> 29:29.001
I could've prevented Tehran.
I could've.

29:29.035 --> 29:31.037
I should've pulled
my agent out.

29:31.070 --> 29:33.205
I knew he was in trouble, and nobody
would listen. What does it matter?

29:33.239 --> 29:34.774
It happened.
It wasn't your fault.

29:34.807 --> 29:37.176
But you came back to D.C.
wound way too tight,

29:37.209 --> 29:40.012
and you took a samurai sword

29:40.046 --> 29:42.782
into the country
coordinator's office.

29:42.815 --> 29:46.052
It was a Civil War saber.

29:46.085 --> 29:49.021
I don't understand. I thought
that you'd be relieved

29:49.055 --> 29:51.323
that I'm out of this.

29:53.059 --> 29:56.228
The director's
very proud of you.

29:56.262 --> 29:57.964
You know, money and supplies
are flowing south.

29:57.997 --> 30:00.733
Contra fighters are back
on the offensive.

30:00.767 --> 30:04.637
This thing is starting to work
just like you knew it would.

30:04.671 --> 30:08.441
He's extremely pleased.

30:08.475 --> 30:10.009
So is the President.

30:16.282 --> 30:17.984
You're full of shit.

30:18.017 --> 30:22.655
He asked us to, uh, pass on
his appreciation

30:22.689 --> 30:25.692
to the responsible parties.

30:37.369 --> 30:41.107
When I was 8,

30:41.140 --> 30:43.309
my dad took me
to the White House

30:43.342 --> 30:46.579
where he was being honored
for his service,

30:46.613 --> 30:50.717
and we had lunch,
and I met Kennedy, and...

30:53.553 --> 30:57.123
That was the proudest moment
of his whole life.

30:57.156 --> 31:00.292
♪♪

31:00.326 --> 31:03.596
I mean, it's in my file.
I know you read it.

31:03.630 --> 31:08.167
Look, I am not
manipulating you, Teddy.

31:08.200 --> 31:12.304
I am just passing on
the, uh, sentiment.

31:12.338 --> 31:13.973
This is working.

31:14.006 --> 31:15.942
Okay, but the question is

31:15.975 --> 31:17.209
is it gonna keep working
because of you,

31:17.243 --> 31:20.412
or do I need to find
somebody else?

31:27.554 --> 31:29.656
(glass clatters)

31:29.689 --> 31:31.858
(door creaks)

31:31.891 --> 31:35.294
Suey! (laughs)

31:35.327 --> 31:37.129
Hey, this place dope, man.

31:37.163 --> 31:39.632
I mean, a few couches,
some lava lamps,

31:39.666 --> 31:41.067
a big screen TV.

31:41.100 --> 31:43.670
Hey, we could a waterbed
in this motherfucka, too.

31:43.703 --> 31:45.572
This ain't no motherfucking
bachelor pad.

31:45.605 --> 31:49.241
It's a goddamn cook house.
Just calm your ass down.

31:49.275 --> 31:51.210
We need to get the gas on
right away.

31:51.243 --> 31:52.745
The stove the whole point.

31:52.779 --> 31:55.381
LOUIE: Can get that done as
early as tomorrow.

31:55.414 --> 31:59.986
(chuckles)
(beeping)

32:00.019 --> 32:01.487
(beeping stops)

32:01.520 --> 32:03.823
Ray-Ray.

32:03.856 --> 32:05.224
(dog barking in distance)

32:05.257 --> 32:08.194
(sighs)

32:08.227 --> 32:11.230
(indistinct conversations)

32:14.433 --> 32:15.768
(engine turns off)

32:17.737 --> 32:20.039
(dog barking in distance)

32:26.078 --> 32:29.081
(siren wails in distance)

32:43.896 --> 32:46.532
We need to talk.

32:46.565 --> 32:50.136
What about?

32:56.275 --> 32:58.344
How to avert a war.

33:00.813 --> 33:03.816
♪♪

33:18.497 --> 33:20.800
Yeah, there we go.

33:20.833 --> 33:24.036
(engine rumbling)

33:26.005 --> 33:27.339
(engine turns off)

33:31.778 --> 33:34.380
(car door closes)

33:38.617 --> 33:40.352
Didn't know you was
bringing somebody.

33:40.386 --> 33:42.621
Just my uncle.

33:44.991 --> 33:48.194
Hold up your end, you ain't
got nothin' to worry about.

33:48.227 --> 33:51.798
Let's just be clear,
I'm not the bitch here.

33:51.831 --> 33:54.767
Whatever the fuck y'all did
to Lenny fucked him up.

33:54.801 --> 33:56.803
Would've got us all killed.

33:56.836 --> 33:58.504
We know.

33:58.537 --> 34:00.740
You're doin' the right thing,
man.

34:03.409 --> 34:04.677
Get 'em out.

34:04.711 --> 34:07.013
I'm-a help you.

34:24.997 --> 34:26.999
(trunk creaks)

34:27.033 --> 34:28.567
Get your ass up.

34:28.600 --> 34:30.870
Get up.

34:32.739 --> 34:35.007
(groans)

34:46.285 --> 34:48.487
Aah! (groans)

34:48.520 --> 34:52.191
(grunts)

34:52.224 --> 34:53.893
Motherfucking Judas.

34:53.926 --> 34:55.327
A'ight, we good?

34:55.361 --> 34:58.497
Afraid we ain't.

34:58.530 --> 35:00.733
Need to know word of this shit
never gonna leave this spot.

35:00.767 --> 35:03.669
(click)

35:03.702 --> 35:05.171
Nah, man. Fuck that, man.

35:05.204 --> 35:06.705
You told me to bring him here.
That's what I did.

35:06.739 --> 35:08.908
Either do it so I know you'll
keep your mouth shut,

35:08.941 --> 35:10.709
or you both dead.

35:10.743 --> 35:12.444
(groans)

35:12.478 --> 35:14.580
-Ray-Ray.
-That wasn't the deal!

35:14.613 --> 35:17.716
-Well, it's the deal now.
-Come on, man.

35:17.750 --> 35:22.254
Hey, man, I understand
this ain't an easy ask.

35:22.288 --> 35:25.792
I know.

35:25.825 --> 35:27.860
Plenty more where
that came from.

35:27.894 --> 35:30.562
We use men who know how
to handle theyselves.

35:32.564 --> 35:34.133
Future could be bright.

35:34.166 --> 35:36.035
Hey.

35:36.068 --> 35:40.306
Hey, hey!
Don't you do this shit for him.

35:40.339 --> 35:41.740
I told you
to let this shit go.

35:41.774 --> 35:44.410
Man, you ain't never gonna
forget this shit.

35:44.443 --> 35:47.713
You won't and you know it.
Look at me, nigga.

35:47.746 --> 35:52.051
Hey! Oh, he thinkin' 'cause
he doin' this shit for you,

35:52.084 --> 35:53.419
that this blood ain't gonna
be on your hands,

35:53.452 --> 35:56.655
but it is, nigga. Ray-Ray!

35:56.688 --> 35:58.324
(groans)

35:58.357 --> 35:59.959
Yeah, you better watch
your back!

35:59.992 --> 36:02.561
-Uh-huh.
-Get the fuck --

36:02.594 --> 36:04.730
(grunts)

36:04.763 --> 36:07.599
-Come on, Ray-Ray.
-Ray-Ray, man, come on!

36:07.633 --> 36:09.268
Come on, man. What the fuck you doin'?
Look at me, man!

36:09.301 --> 36:11.270
-Do it, motherfucka!
-All right, all right!

36:11.303 --> 36:12.438
-Ray-Ray!
-Do it!

36:12.471 --> 36:15.141
Ray-Ray! Ray --

36:15.174 --> 36:18.210
(gurgling sound)

36:35.794 --> 36:38.064
For Leon, motherfucka.

36:50.742 --> 36:52.578
(gun rattles)

36:55.848 --> 36:58.985
You ever wanna make some ends,
you know where to find me.

36:59.018 --> 37:02.021
♪♪

37:09.095 --> 37:10.997
(engine starts)

37:11.030 --> 37:13.900
(gravel crunches)

37:23.675 --> 37:26.678
(indistinct conversations)

37:31.951 --> 37:34.386
(exhales slowly)

37:40.692 --> 37:42.294
(latches click)

37:43.695 --> 37:45.431
(latches click)

37:48.134 --> 37:50.269
(exhales deeply)

37:56.042 --> 38:00.646
(clearing throat)

38:03.549 --> 38:06.118
(speaking Spanish)

38:16.562 --> 38:19.966
(inhales and exhales)

38:19.999 --> 38:23.069
(exhales deeply)

38:26.338 --> 38:29.942
(click)
(speaking Spanish)

38:32.111 --> 38:35.081
Mm.

38:35.114 --> 38:38.217
Diego...

38:38.250 --> 38:41.153
(speaking Spanish)

38:56.035 --> 38:58.104
(paper rustles)
Diego...

38:58.137 --> 39:00.006
(utensil clatters)

39:00.039 --> 39:02.141
(chewing)

39:11.383 --> 39:13.352
Hi.

39:13.385 --> 39:16.022
Hi. How are you?

39:16.055 --> 39:19.025
I'm fantastic. How are you?

39:19.058 --> 39:21.627
-American?
-Oh, absolutely.

39:24.830 --> 39:26.432
(punch lands)
(speaks Spanish)

39:26.465 --> 39:28.767
-Okay, okay, hold on, hold on.
-Explain this shit!

39:28.800 --> 39:30.502
O-obviously, you're upset.

39:30.536 --> 39:32.371
Okay, you have
every right to be.

39:32.404 --> 39:35.941
But just -- okay, please just
put the gun down

39:35.974 --> 39:37.709
and we could talk.

39:41.513 --> 39:43.282
(all shouting in Spanish)

39:43.315 --> 39:46.852
Alejandro Usteves.
(exhales deeply)

39:46.885 --> 39:47.986
What was that?

39:48.020 --> 39:50.822
Alejandro Usteves.

39:50.856 --> 39:54.326
Okay. (exhales deeply)

39:54.360 --> 39:56.428
You're here to make
a deal with him, right?

39:57.896 --> 39:59.865
Alejandro was already
bringing cocaine

39:59.898 --> 40:01.700
into the United States.

40:01.733 --> 40:03.969
He just needed DEA assistance
to get it across the border.

40:04.002 --> 40:07.139
You two are gonna be
bargaining chips.

40:07.173 --> 40:08.674
He was setting you up.

40:15.781 --> 40:19.218
I know that the same way I know
everything about you two.

40:20.886 --> 40:23.889
I know that you like being
in the United States.

40:23.922 --> 40:26.392
And I know that the Orejuelas
trust you and leave you alone

40:26.425 --> 40:28.394
as long as the money keeps
rolling in.

40:28.427 --> 40:31.097
And I can ensure that
that continues to happen.

40:31.130 --> 40:34.266
Keep the DEA and local
law enforcement off your ass,

40:34.300 --> 40:36.001
provide you with intel
about your competitors

40:36.034 --> 40:38.837
and security
at certain border points.

40:38.870 --> 40:41.773
What do we have to do for you?

40:41.807 --> 40:45.611
Well, you have to provide me
with absolutely pure cocaine

40:45.644 --> 40:48.414
at prices that's gonna make
your balls hurt.

40:48.447 --> 40:50.616
Who the fuck are you, man?

40:50.649 --> 40:53.919
Doesn't matter who I am.

40:53.952 --> 40:56.255
Only matters who I represent.

40:56.288 --> 40:58.590
And who's that?

40:58.624 --> 41:00.726
The United States government.

41:07.333 --> 41:10.902
(coughs and sniffles)

41:10.936 --> 41:12.704
(elevator bell dings)

41:12.738 --> 41:15.707
(indistinct conversations)

41:15.741 --> 41:18.777
♪♪

41:20.946 --> 41:23.315
(indistinct conversations
in Spanish)

41:23.349 --> 41:26.352
(woman singing in Spanish)

41:27.986 --> 41:32.124
(speaking Spanish)

41:32.158 --> 41:35.194
♪♪

42:07.993 --> 42:10.529
Sí.

42:27.078 --> 42:29.515
You have to help me out.
You have to back me up.

42:29.548 --> 42:32.718
-I can't do that.
-Why not?

43:02.180 --> 43:06.352
-(scoffs)
-Mija...

43:35.747 --> 43:39.851
("Fantasy"
by Earth, Wind & Fire playing)

43:39.885 --> 43:42.421
All right, all right, all right,
give it up, give it up.

43:42.454 --> 43:43.889
How much we make today?
Brothers?

43:43.922 --> 43:46.392
-Oh.
-Man, what'd I tell you?

43:46.425 --> 43:50.128
Put the 1's in front of the 5's,
right, and the 20's in the back.

43:50.161 --> 43:52.097
Hey, y'all paying attention?

43:52.130 --> 43:53.632
This is where it starts,
you hear me?

43:53.665 --> 43:55.767
All right, then.

43:55.801 --> 43:57.703
♪ Every man has a place Which one
of y'all messed up my count?

43:57.736 --> 44:00.606
(speaks indistinctly)
♪ In his heart there's a space

44:00.639 --> 44:03.259
♪ And the world can't erase
his fantasies ♪ Tell

44:03.284 --> 44:05.611
the brothers to stop
messing with my money.

44:05.644 --> 44:08.480
♪ Take a ride in the sky

44:08.514 --> 44:10.882
♪ On our ship fantasize

44:10.916 --> 44:17.489
♪ All your dreams will come true
right away ♪

44:17.523 --> 44:21.993
(children shouting playfully)
♪ And we will live together

44:22.027 --> 44:25.297
♪ Until the twelfth of never

44:25.331 --> 44:27.766
(cheering) All right, all right,
all right, who's got money?

44:27.799 --> 44:29.401
You got money? You got money?

44:29.435 --> 44:32.170
Y'all kids gotta learn
nothin' in life is free.

44:32.203 --> 44:37.142
Who's got money? You got money?
You, you, you?

44:37.175 --> 44:38.977
